{"/service/ndnp/dlc/batch_dlc_queenofspades_ver01/data/sn83045462/00280608737/1958032701/0993.xml":{"full_text":"A-14\nTHE EVENING STAR, Washington, D. C.\nTHURSDAY. MARCH ST. IMA\nWheaton Store Planned\nBy Woodward Lothrop\nBy DONALD B. HADLEY\nStar Financial Editor\nWoodward Lothrop has completed negotiations for\na $3 million suburban store, which it expects to open at\nWheaton, Md., in the fall of next year, President Andrew\nParker announced last night.\nA long-term lease has been signed for a store of 150,000\nsquare feet to be constructed in the Wheaton Plaza, regional\nshopping center being developed\nby Eastern Shopping Centers,\nInc. The center will occupy\nan 80-acre tract along the\nsouth side of Vlers Mill road\nbetween Georgia avenue and\nUniversity boulevard, west\nThe new air-conditioned store\nwill have three floors and will\nInclude a community audito\nrium. Its Colonial design will\nbe similar to architecture of\nWoodward Lothrop stores in\nChevy Chase, Bethesda, Alex\nandria and Seven Corners and\nwill set the pattern for other\nStores in the center.\nConstruction of the new de\npartment store is expected to\nstart in June. It will be the\nlargest unit in the center.\nSpace for 55 other stores will\nbe provided along with parking\nfor 5.000 cars. A Giant Food\ngupermarket, a Hot Shoppe\nrestaurant and a gasoline serv\nice station already have been\nopened in the center.\nEastern Shopping Centers,\nInc., rental agent for Wheaton\nPlaza, has headquarters in\nYonkers, N. Y. It also is de\nveloping the Prince Georges\nPlaza shopping center in Uni\nversity Park, Md.\nWheaton Plaza is situated\nalong the south side of the\nWheaton triangle and is near\nthe heart of a rapidly growing\nsection of Montgomery County.\nOverseas Consumer Credit\nCalled Promising Field\nMaj. Gen. George Olmsted,\nUSAR, president of Internation\nal Bank, of Washington, yester\nday said his institution, the\nMorris Plan Corp. and other\nprivate organizations are pre\npared to subscribe necessary\ncapital to form a corporation!\nto extend consumer credit over\nseas.\nAppearing before the House\nForeign Affairs Committee on\nthe mutual security program.\nGen. Olmsted said such a firm,\nwhich might be called the In\nternational Consumer Credit\nCorp., could establish a Morris\nPlan type of operation in for\neign countries and meet an un\nfilled need.\nGEICO Holders Approve\nIncrease in Capital\nStockholders of Government\nEmployees Insurance Co. yes\nterday approved an increase in\ncapital stock to 1.6 million\nshares from 750.000 to pave the\nway for a 100 per cent stock\ndividend.\nPayments of the stock divi-\ndend will increase outstanding\n667,285 shares of $4 par stock l\nto 1,334,570. The company will\nMUTUAL FUNDS j\nNEW YORK, Mir. IT UPt.-AitiMil Israeli,\ntin Sicnnt.es Diilirs. lie., mi iiititiMi.\nlil Rshet 111 Islet,\nMtrliFnll.il 1.8 tnurtt FI 1.21 11.11;\nAffiltl FI 5.13 1.11 IKIIM FI 1.7! i.\u00bb'\nBusi SI 1.0 4.11 lint FI 11.41 11.13\nIn Mil FI 7.U Ml lltl Its FI 3.44 3.71\nAssoc FI Tr 1.33 1.8 lioCtAntr I.H 1.11;\nAt Dm Mot 4.43 4.14 In Tr Bis I.M 1.11\nAit HFI A 4.17 1.41 Itltl FI 21.M21.Hj\nAll HFI I 7.11 7.77 'llltstlt 11.14 11.14\nAlt HSt FI I.M 3.71 KEYSTONE:\nAll sci I El I.U II.M Cist 11 21.11 21.21\nAl Tom Cl 21.71 22.72 Ctsf 11 22.43 24.47\n111 Rl Mit 11.17 11.15 Cist I 3 11.11 II.M\n\u2022I It TA* 11.17 21.11 Cut I 4 I.M 1.11\n\u25a0istll FI 14.12 11.12 Cist R 17. N I.M\n\u2022rl It In 21.71 22. M Cist K 2 1.71 W.SW\n\u25a0llltck FI 11.32 12.41 Cist 3 1 14.8 13.11\nCalif Fill 1.11 7.M Cut 3 2 1.71 lI.M\nCM 111 FI 11.14 12.14 Cist S 1 11.14 11.31!\nCiMli FI lI.M 17.31 Cist 34 7.27 7.8\nCli lit Ir 1.11 7.11 Fill Cm I.M 11.71\nCm Vnt 4.17 1,12, Kliektr FI 1.11 1.17,\nCut SI 1r 22.12 21.11 Ltlill Tr 11.41 11.47,\nCkta Fill 11.71 17.11 ltlill Vnt I.M 111\nCtl Fill 111 132 Lift li in 14.14 11. M\nClaw lit 7.77 1.41 lit! Ii St 1.21 1.74\nClaw in I.M 1.12 \u2018las S M 41. M 41. N\nClaw St FI t 1.12 12.13 MANAt FUND:\nCia 